defs.name: Covenant
defs.value: Covenant::{None, Claim, Bid, Open, Reveal, Redeem, Register, Update, Renew, Transfer, Finalize, Revoke}
defs.docs: A Handshake covenant, which is a method of changing name state on the chain.

defs.name: name_hash
defs.docs: The hash of the name for the Open.

defs.name: height
defs.docs:
The height at which the bid occured
The height should always be 0 for an Open.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: The raw name that the open is for.

defs.name: FinalizeCovenant
defs.value: FinalizeCovenant { name_hash, height, name, flags, block_hash }

defs.name: BlockHeader
defs.value: BlockHeader { version, prev_blockhash, merkle_root, witness_root, tree_root, filter_root, reserved_root, time, bits, nonce }
defs.docs:
A block header, which contains all the block's information except
 the actual transactions

defs.name: prev_blockhash
defs.docs: Reference to the previous block in the chain

defs.name: merkle_root
defs.docs: The root hash of the merkle tree of transactions in the block

defs.name: tree_root
defs.docs: The root hash of the Urkel Tree of name states in the block

defs.name: filter_root
defs.docs: The root hash of the bloom filter XXX Need more here.

defs.name: reserved_root
defs.docs: A root reserved for future implementation of Neutrino on the protocol level

defs.name: time
defs.docs: The timestamp of the block, as claimed by the miner

defs.name: bits
defs.docs:
The target value below which the blockhash must lie, encoded as a
 a float (with well-defined rounding, of course)
 This should probably be a Compact type - See Parity Bitcoin //TODO

defs.name: nonce
defs.docs: The nonce, selected to obtain a low enough blockhash

defs.name: null
defs.docs: Returns a null Outpoint for use in coinbase transactions.

defs.name: version
defs.docs: The protocol version, is currently expected to be 1 or 2 (BIP 68).

defs.name: lock_time
defs.docs:
Block number before which this transaction is valid, or 0 for
 valid immediately.
